\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 MEYER LEMON MARMALADE\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs34 \cf0 MAKES  6 (1/2-PINT) JARS\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs30 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa80\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs34 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}6 Meyer lemons (1 1/2 lb)\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups water\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups sugar\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\b\fs32 \cf3 {\listtext	\'95	}SPECIAL EQUIPMENT: 
\b0\fs34 \cf0 Cheesecloth, Kitchen string, 6 (1/2-pint) Mason-type jars, sterilized\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Halve lemons crosswise and remove seeds. Tie seeds in a cheesecloth bag. Quarter each lemon half and thinly slice. Combine with bag of seeds and water in a 5-quart nonreactive heavy pot and let mixture stand, covered, at room temperature 24 hours.
\fs28 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs34 {\listtext	\'95	}Bring lemon mixture to a boil over moderate heat. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until reduced to 4 cups, about 45 minutes. Stir in sugar and boil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally and skimming off any foam, until a teaspoon of mixture dropped on a cold plate gels, about 15 minutes.
\fs28 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs34 {\listtext	\'95	}Ladle hot marmalade into jars, filling to within 1/4 inch of top. Wipe rims with dampened cloth and seal jars with lids.
\fs28 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs34 {\listtext	\'95	}Put jars in a water-bath canner or on a rack set in a deep pot. Add enough hot water to cover jars by 1 inch and bring to a boil. Boil jars, covered, 5 minutes and transfer with tongs to a rack. Cool jars completely.
\fs28 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs34 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Marmalade keeps, stored in a cool, dark place, up to 1 year.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \

\b\fs32 \cf3 TO STERILIZE JARS FOR PRESERVING
\b0\fs34 \cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Wash jars in hot suds and rinse in hot water. Put jars in a water-bath canner or on a rack set in a deep pot and cover with water. Bring water to a boil and boil jars, covered, 15 minutes from time steam emerges from pot. Turn off heat and add lids. Let jars and lids stand in hot water 10 minutes.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Lift 1 jar from hot water with tongs and fill without drying. Lift both sections of 1 lid from hot water and screw on jar without drying. Repeat procedure for remaining jars and lids.}